{"title": "Pirate, and The Three Cutters", "description": "Pirates are the subject of many a dime novel and boys' stories, but they tend to be portrayed as one-dimensional. Such is the case here. The captain of The Avenger is a Byronic or even a Michael Scottish hero\u2014an impossible monster, compounded of one virtue and a thousand crimes.  Marryat drew on his recollections of the time when he was a midshipman with Cochrane in the Imp\u00e8rieuse, for the figure of the old steersman, who sticks to his post under the fire of the Avenger.\r\nThe Three Cutters was written to pad out the novel The Pirate and deals with smuggling. It is a farcical romp, with too many women in a man's world to be credible. ", "duration": 30279, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "297", "name": "Frederick Marryat"}], "coverArt": "https://archive.org/download/pirate_2203_librivox/pirates_3_cutters_2203.jpg", "copyright_year": "1897", "genres": ["Action & Adventure Fiction", "Nautical & Marine Fiction"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "LibriVox Volunteers"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "Lynne T"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "Lynne T"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "sati"}], "sections": [{"section": 0, "title": "Introduction", "readers": [16328], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/pirate_2203_librivox/pirate_00_marryat_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1072}, {"section": 1, "title": "The Bay of Biscay", "readers": [12980], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/pirate_2203_librivox/pirate_01_marryat_64kb.mp3", "duration": 832}, {"section": 2, "title": "The Bachelor", "readers": [12980], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/pirate_2203_librivox/pirate_02_marryat_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1305}, {"section": 3, "title": "The Gale", "readers": [16990], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/pirate_2203_librivox/pirate_03_marryat_64kb.mp3", "duration": 670}, {"section": 4, "title": "The Leak", "readers": [16990], "path": "https://www.archive.org/do